    <text id="B0343T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Hall informs Jackson about some restrictions on evidence in a case involving the
                    Methodist Episcopal Church in Staunton.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <abbr expan="Bureau of Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands">B.R.F. &amp;
                        A.L.</abbr> Office 3<hi rend="super">d</hi>
                    <abbr expan="Division">Div</abbr> 9<hi rend="super">t</hi> Sub <abbr
                        expan="District">Dist</abbr>
                    <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Thomas">Thos</abbr> P. Jackson, <abbr
                            expan="Agent">Ag<hi rend="super">t</hi>.</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1867-07-22">July 22d 1867</date>
                        <name type="place">Woodstock, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>Please inform the parties (through council) to the suit of the <abbr
                        expan="Methodist Episcopal">M.E.</abbr> Church in Staunton, that <hi
                        rend="underline">no</hi> evidence will be heard in the case, except that
                    reduced to writing, also, that council can argue the case, if they so desire,
                    the hearing of which has been deferred until July 31st 1867.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Respectfully<lb/>Your <abbr expan="obedient">obt</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="Servant">Servt</abbr></salute>
                    <signed>J.T.H. Hall<lb/><abbr expan="Lieutenant">Lt</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="Veterans Reserve Corps">V.R.C.</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="Acting Assistant Adjutant General"
                        >A.A.A.G.</abbr><lb/>&amp; <abbr expan="Military Commissioner">Mil
                        Comr</abbr></signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
